      },
      "name": "Gmail Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.gmailTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [250, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "string": [
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "hiddenlayer.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "bah.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "credo.ai" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "guardrailsai.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "holisticai.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "dynamo.ai" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "lmco.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "ngc.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "palantir.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "iqt.org" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "saif.vc" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "jpmorgan.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "wellsfargo.com" },
            { "value1": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}", "operation": "contains", "value2": "citi.com" }
          ],
          "combineOperation": "any"
        }
      },
      "name": "Filter Outreach Contacts",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.filter",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [470, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "http://127.0.0.1:8001/v1/governance/scan",
        "method": "POST",
        "body": {
          "json": {
            "text": "={{ $json.text }}",
            "source": "email_inbound",
            "sender": "={{ $json.from.value[0].address }}"
          }
        }
      },
      "name": "Governance Scan",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [690, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "https://router.huggingface.co/v1/chat/completions",
        "method": "POST",
        "headers": {
          "string": [
            { "name": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{ $env.HF_TOKEN }}" },
            { "name": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
          ]
        },
        "body": {
          "json": {
            "model": "issdandavis/scbe-pivot-qwen-0.5b",
            "messages": [
              {
                "role": "system",
                "content": "You are Issac Davis's business assistant drafting email replies. Use this context for every reply:\n\nSCBE-AETHERMOORE: AI governance framework using hyperbolic geometry + post-quantum cryptography.\nPatent: USPTO #63/961,403 (pending)\nWebsite: https://aethermoorgames.com\nGitHub: https://github.com/issdandavis/SCBE-AETHERMOORE\nHuggingFace: https://huggingface.co/issdandavis\nDataset: 233K multi-view SFT pairs (cleaned to 41K, 24 categories)\nTests: 6,742 passing (5,957 TS + 785 Python), 100% crypto pass rate\nBenchmarks: 85.7% detection at 0% FP, 91/91 vs industry 62/91, F1 0.813\nPricing: Pump API $49/mo, Pro $199/mo, GaaS $499/mo\nBook: The Six Tongues Protocol on Amazon\nLive demos: https://aethermoorgames.com/demos/\nEnterprise: https://aethermoorgames.com/enterprise.html\n\nFour pillars no competitor has: (1) PQC (ML-KEM-768 + ML-DSA-65), (2) Hyperbolic cost scaling H(d,R)=R^(d^2), (3) Multi-agent coordination security (14-layer pipeline), (4) Inference-time guardrails.\n\nTone: Professional, direct, confident but not arrogant. Issac is a solo founder in Port Angeles, WA. Position as complement, not competitor. Always offer a demo or technical briefing as next step."
